events.message:
Add std::optional support to Boost's equality check

Also moved the operators to the bottom of the file since they're less important and to group them together.

Note that we're never writing optionals on the right side, e.g.
> BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(uint256::FromUserHex(""), std::make_optional(uint256::ZERO));
since they can simply be either:
> BOOST_CHECK_EQUAL(uint256::FromUserHex(""), uint256::ZERO);
or if empty:
> BOOST_CHECK(!uint256::FromUserHex(""));

Co-authored-by: Hodlinator <172445034+hodlinator@users.noreply.github.com>

